<L>__{interior the house chamber dawn}
<A>__{the chamber is quiet and dark. pages and clerks prepare the desks, laying out pens and paper, filling inkwells. title: the morning of the vote}
<D>__{january 31, 1865}
<A>__{a clerk is draping red white and blue bunting on the desks of representatives from seceded states. these will of course remain unoccupied during the vote. the first congressman to arrive, thaddeus stevens clumps in. he goes to his desk and sits. he looks around the empty chamber, ready and waiting.}
